---+ Nico Erbs

Master Thesis Student since May 2009.

"Extracting the Learner's Opinions: Bootstrapping Extraction Patterns for Sentiment Analysis"

<blockquote style="border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(251, 251, 251) rgb(251, 251, 251) rgb(251, 251, 251) rgb(221, 221, 221); border-width: 1px 0px 1px 3px; padding: 0.5em 1.25em; background-color: #fbfbfb"><strong style="font-weight: bold">Abstract:</strong> Forums, as well as any Web 2.0 platforms, offer anybody an excellent way to express their opininion or distribute suggestions. In this Masterhesis my aim is to develop a system that automatically analyses whether an entry in a forum is expressing an opinion (subjective) or is presenting facts (objective). Additionally it should point out if the opinion is either positive, neutral or negative (polarity) and retrieve the target of the opinion.
The system should be as modular as possible and all components should be exchangeable. The system should be implemented as UIMA components.</blockquote>

